Created files:
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Connection/ConnectionStateMachine.cs
    Pure C# state machine for the 5-state connection lifecycle
    (Disconnected / Connecting / Connected / Reconnecting /
    PermanentlyDisconnected). Single-entry transition API:
        - public ConnectionState CurrentState { get; }
        - public bool ShutdownRequested { get; }
        - public event Action<ConnectionState, ConnectionState>? StateChanged
        - public bool TryTransition(ConnectionState target, bool isShutdown = false)
    Constructor accepts an optional Action<string> logWarning for
    invalid-transition diagnostics (the ClientSessionManager / runtime
    composition will wire this to CoreIpcLogger in later tasks).

    Transition matrix (the 8 valid paths from design Flow 3):
        1. Disconnected     -> Connecting
        2. Connecting       -> Connected
        3. Connecting       -> Disconnected         (handshake fail)
        4. Connected        -> Reconnecting         (socket drop)
        5. Connected        -> Disconnected         (Shutdown path)
        6. Reconnecting     -> Connecting           (backoff expired)
        7. Reconnecting     -> PermanentlyDisconnected (max attempts)
        8. Reconnecting     -> Disconnected         (Shutdown path)
    All other targets are invalid transitions: TryTransition returns
    false, fires no event, and emits a single warning via the supplied
    callback. Same-state transitions are silent no-ops (no event,
    no warning) so that idempotent calls are safe.

    Shutdown semantics (Req 5.8):
        - Pass isShutdown=true together with target=Disconnected to
          mark the machine as shutdown-initiated. The ShutdownRequested
          sticky flag is set even when the machine is already at
          Disconnected (no event fires in that case).
        - Once ShutdownRequested is true, any subsequent transition
          to Connecting is rejected (returns false + warning),
          structurally suppressing reconnect attempts after PlayMode
          stop / app quit.
        - isShutdown=true with any target other than Disconnected is
          rejected and logged; this enforces the diagram's contract
          that shutdown is always a clean disconnect.

    Thread safety: an internal lock guards _state and
    _shutdownRequested. StateChanged is invoked outside the lock to
    avoid re-entrant deadlocks with subscribers that call CurrentState.

