Implementation summary:
- ConnectionStateMachine sits in the new
  VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Connection namespace, inside the
  existing VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. It is pure C# with
  no Unity engine references, so the EditMode tests construct and
  drive it directly without any PlayerLoop or MonoBehaviour
  dependency. ClientSessionManager (task 3.3), CoreIpcDiagnostics
  (task 5.4) and CoreIpcRuntime (task 6.3) compose this state
  machine via the StateChanged event in later tasks.
- The transition matrix is a single static IsValidTransition switch
  so the table is centralized and easy to audit against the design
  Flow 3 state diagram. PermanentlyDisconnected is terminal: only
  isShutdown=true on Disconnected target (no-op + flag set) is
  accepted from there; everything else falls through the invalid
  branch with a warning.
- ShutdownRequested is sticky: once set it cannot be cleared and
  acts as the structural guard for Req 5.8 (PlayMode stop / app
  quit must never trigger reconnect). The reconnect-suppression
  check sits before the matrix check so the warning message
  distinguishes "blocked by shutdown" from "invalid transition".

